The director may establish by rule standards applicable to transporters of hazardous waste identified or listed under this chapter including, but not limited to, requirements regarding:



	(1)	Obtaining an identification number;
	(2)	Labeling practices;
	(3)	Transporting hazardous waste;
	(4)	Requiring action, including cleanup, if hazardous waste is discharged in transit;
	(5)	Using the manifest properly; and
	(6)	Submitting reports and recordkeeping practices. [L 1989, c 212, pt of §5]




Cross References
  Transportation of hazardous materials, hazardous waste, and etiologic agents, see §§286-221 to 227.
